  "question": "A 2 week old baby is referred to the surgical team by the paediatricians. They are concerned because the child has a painful area of macerated tissue at the site of the umbilicus. On examination, a clear- yellowish fluid is seen to be draining from the umbilicus when the baby cries. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
